      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-01-pump-hemolysis-benchmark",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FDA pump hemolysis benchmark comparison — all 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA benchmark experimental data at 5 flow-speed operating points. RH < 1 achieved at all points. The UQ campaign (Latin hypercube sampling, n=128) was embedded within this validation activity and confirmed that parameter uncertainty contributes less than 4% variation to the RH metric, supporting the adequacy conclusion. Structured sensitivity analysis results are reported in the UQ campaign narrative appendix."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-02-mesh-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 3.2M, medium 7.8M, fine 16.4M cells) using Richardson extrapolation. Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH: 2.1% (medium-to-fine transition). Discretization error deemed acceptable for MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-03-code-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Numerical code verification — method of manufactured solutions",
      "description": "MMS verification of the Navier-Stokes solver and power-law hemolysis transport equation. Observed order of accuracy consistent with nominal second-order scheme. No systematic errors identified in hemolysis scalar transport implementation."
    }
  ],
