      "rationale": "NIH and RH are the quantities mandated by FDA guidance for CPB hemolysis assessment. Validation QoI directly maps to the COU decision metric. No surrogate quantities used. Traceability table linking model outputs to submission requirements included in the credibility evidence package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must cover the geometry class, flow regime, and hemolysis mechanism representative of the CPB device COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump — the same geometry class as the subject CPB device. Reynolds number range (Re 2,000–18,000) and shear-stress exposure times in validation experiments bracket the COU operating envelope. Power-law hemolysis model validated for shear-dominated red cell damage consistent with CPB conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals must reach target convergence criteria; not formally assessed at MRL 2 beyond standard practice.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 with medium model influence, formal numerical solver error assessment beyond standard residual monitoring is not required. Residuals converged to 1e-5 for continuity and momentum; hemolysis scalar to 1e-6. No assessment beyond standard practice performed; scoped consistent with MRL 2 expectations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Use error assessment not required at MRL 2 for medium model influence COU.",
      "rationale": "MRL 2 with medium model influence does not mandate formal use error assessment. Standard operator qualification and simulation protocol review performed informally. No structured use-error analysis conducted; consistent with MRL 2 scoping."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The chosen turbulence and hemolysis model forms must be justified relative to the flow physics and supported by literature evidence for similar pump geometries.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on documented superior performance for rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients (Menter 1994; Hariharan et al. 2011). Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) appropriate for shear-dominated CPB conditions. Model form selection documented with literature support and sensitivity to turbulence model choice assessed qualitatively in the UQ campaign narrative."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) must be traceable to measurement data or manufacturer specifications with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry from FDA benchmark CAD files (CDRH repository). Fluid properties (density 1056 kg/m3, viscosity 3.5 cP) from experimental characterisation with ±5% uncertainty bounds. Inlet velocity profiles from PIV measurements. All inputs archived with provenance metadata. Input uncertainty propagated through the UQ campaign (128-sample LHS) confirming RH sensitivity below 4% across the input uncertainty space."
    },
